Harleyâ€™s 384-well MIC Analysis Pipeline

User setup

This pipeline is for analyzing 384-well MICs. See figure 1 for required plate layout. You can have any number of drugs between 1-14 as long as your replicates are in the orientation of the image and your gradients occupy columns 2-12 and 13-23. You can also run the code on gradients that move from right to left as well by choosing the proper gradient option below.

Figure 1

Label the drugs you are using from top left (up to 7 on left side of plate, and 7 more on right side).

drugs<-c('Drug1', 'Drug2', 'Drug3', 'Drug4', 'Drug5', 'Drug6', 'Drug7', 'Drug8','Drug9','Drug10','Drug11','Drug12')

Specify your condition (Alamar Blue or OD600), and also your maximum concentration in Î¼M.

condition<-'Alamar Blue'
max_conc=25

Define your Gradient orientation.

#use this gradient if max conc on right side of plate!
gradient<-c(0,max_conc/512,max_conc/256,max_conc/128,max_conc/64,max_conc/32,max_conc/16,max_conc/8,max_conc/4,max_conc/2,max_conc)
#use this gradient if max conc on left side of plate (as in figure)!
gradient<-c(max_conc,max_conc/2,max_conc/4,max_conc/8,max_conc/16,max_conc/32,max_conc/64,max_conc/128,max_conc/256,max_conc/512,0)

Read in your raw plate data as portrayed. Just save the complete matrix as a CSV file (all rows and columns without row or column names).

data<-read.csv('~/Desktop/plate.csv', header=F)

Data Processing

Background Subtraction

First background subtraction.

data<-as.matrix(data)
#subtract BG
media_BG<-mean(data[,24])
data<-data-media_BG
BG_Sub<-data

Normalization to no-drug average

nodrug_average<-mean(c(data[,1],data[,12],data[,23]))
data<-data/nodrug_average
Norm_data<-data

Calculating Mean and SD

#this procedure occurs in two steps because the plate is in halves, and then combines afterwards
merged_dataframe<-as.data.frame(gradient)
rep_1<-2
rep_2<-3
drugs_left_plate<-drugs[1:7]

for(i in 1:length(drugs_left_plate)){
    matrix_list<-list(as.matrix(data[rep_1,2:12]), as.matrix(data[rep_2,2:12]))
    drug_1_avg<-apply(simplify2array(matrix_list), 1:2, mean)
    colnames(drug_1_avg)<-drugs_left_plate[i]
    rownames(drug_1_avg)<-gradient
    drug_1_SD<-apply(simplify2array(matrix_list), 1:2, sd) # calculate SD of two matrices
    colnames(drug_1_SD)<-paste0(drugs_left_plate[i], '_SD')
    rownames(drug_1_SD)<-gradient
    #now write data continuously to dataframe as I move through it
    drug_dataframe<-as.data.frame(drug_1_avg)
    SD_dataframe<-as.data.frame(drug_1_SD)
    merged_dataframe<-cbind(merged_dataframe, drug_dataframe, SD_dataframe)

    rep_1<-rep_1+2
    rep_2<-rep_2+2
  
}

#--------do same for right side of plate
merged_dataframe_right<-as.data.frame(gradient)
rep_1<-2
rep_2<-3
drugs_right_plate<-drugs[8:length(drugs)]
#issue is that when I get past the first 7 drugs and I need to do second half of plate
#maybe I should split drugs into two sets of, first set is 1- up to 7, second set is 8-14

for(i in 1:length(drugs_right_plate)){
  matrix_list<-list(as.matrix(data[rep_1,13:23]), as.matrix(data[rep_2,13:23]))
  drug_1_avg<-apply(simplify2array(matrix_list), 1:2, mean)
  colnames(drug_1_avg)<-drugs_right_plate[i]
  rownames(drug_1_avg)<-gradient
  drug_1_SD<-apply(simplify2array(matrix_list), 1:2, sd) # calculate SD of two matrices
  colnames(drug_1_SD)<-paste0(drugs_right_plate[i], '_SD')
  rownames(drug_1_SD)<-gradient
  #now write data continuously to dataframe as I move through it
  drug_dataframe<-as.data.frame(drug_1_avg)
  SD_dataframe<-as.data.frame(drug_1_SD)
  merged_dataframe_right<-cbind(merged_dataframe_right, drug_dataframe, SD_dataframe)
  
  rep_1<-rep_1+2
  rep_2<-rep_2+2
  
}

#combine left and right plate half data
merge<-cbind(merged_dataframe,merged_dataframe_right)
merge$gradient<-NULL

Reformat Data For Plotting & Export

merge_drugs<-merge[,drugs]
merge_drugs['conc']<-gradient
merge_SD<-merge[,paste0(drugs, '_SD')]
merge_SD['conc']<-gradient
#-----------------
data_long <- gather(merge_drugs, condition, measurement,1:length(drugs), factor_key=TRUE)
data_long_SD <- gather(merge_SD, condition, SD,1:length(drugs), factor_key=TRUE)
merged_long<-cbind(data_long, data_long_SD)
colnames(merged_long)<-c('Conc', 'Treatment', 'Reading', 'conc2', 'conc3', 'SD')
merged_long$conc2<-NULL
merged_long$conc3<-NULL

Calculate MICs

#MIC50
drugs_df<-as.data.frame(drugs)
drugs_df['MIC50']<-NA
drugs_df['MIC80']<-NA

for (i in 1:length(drugs)){
  MIC<-merged_long$Conc[merged_long$Treatment == drugs[i] & merged_long$Reading < 0.5]
  if (length(MIC) > 0){
    drugs_df$MIC50[i]<-min(MIC)
  }
  else if (length(MIC) == 0){
    drugs_df$MIC50[i]<-paste0('>', max_conc)
  }
  
}
#MIC80
for (i in 1:length(drugs)){
  MIC<-merged_long$Conc[merged_long$Treatment == drugs[i] & merged_long$Reading < 0.2]
  if (length(MIC) > 0){
    drugs_df$MIC80[i]<-min(MIC)
  }
  else if (length(MIC) == 0){
    drugs_df$MIC80[i]<-paste0('>', max_conc)
  }
  
}

Plotting

Plot MICs as Dose Response Curves

#axes set based on condition
if (grepl('OD', condition)){
  ylabel<-'Relative Growth\n'
}
if (!grepl('OD', condition)){
  ylabel<-'Relative Metabolic Activity\n'
}

#if you want to subset out certain drugs to plot, just change first line of ggplot code to use merged_long_sub instead

manual_colors<-RColorBrewer::brewer.pal(length(drugs_left_plate), 'Set1')
manual_colors2<-RColorBrewer::brewer.pal(length(drugs_right_plate), 'Set2')
lots_of_colors<-c(manual_colors, manual_colors2)



CairoPDF(file=paste0("MIC_",condition,'_',format(Sys.time(), '%a-%b-%d-%H-%M'),".pdf"),width = 17, height=10)
ggplot(merged_long, aes(x=Conc,group=Treatment, fill=Treatment, color=Treatment)) +
  Cleanup+
  #makes a line plot for desired well
  geom_line(aes(y=Reading), size=rel(2))+
  geom_point(aes(y=Reading), size=rel(3), color='gray0')+
  geom_errorbar(aes(ymax = Reading + SD, ymin=Reading - SD), width = 0.05, color='gray0')+
  ggtitle(paste0(condition,' \nDose Response Curve'))+
  ylab(ylabel) + 
  xlab("\nCompound Concentration (Î¼M)")+
  scale_fill_manual(values=lots_of_colors)+
  
  theme(axis.line.x= element_line(colour="black"),
        axis.line.y=element_line(colour='black'),
        axis.title.y = element_text(face="bold", size=rel(2), color='black'), 
        axis.text.y = element_text(face="bold", size=rel(2), color='black'),
        axis.title.x = element_text(face="bold", size=rel(2), color='black'), 
        axis.text.x = element_text(face='bold', size=rel(2), color='black'),
        plot.title = element_text(face='bold', size=rel(3), hjust=0.5, color='black'),
        legend.text=element_text(size=rel(2)),
        legend.title=element_text(size=rel(2)),
        plot.margin = unit(c(2,2,2,2), units = 'cm'),
        legend.position = 'right', 
        legend.key.size = unit(1, 'cm'))+
  scale_x_continuous(trans='log10', breaks=c(0.1,1,10,50))+
  scale_y_continuous(breaks=c(0, 0.25, 0.5, 0.75, 1,1.25))
